==English==
===Etymology===
From Old and modern French ''[[unifier]]'' or late Latin ''[[unificare]]''

===Verb===
{{conj|unify|unifies|unified|unified|unifying}}
# ''(transitive)'' Cause to become [[one]]; make into a [[unit]]; [[consolidate]]; [[merge]]; [[combine]].
# ''(intransitive)'' Become one.

